definition.value: Any organosulfur compound with structure R'C(R)SH in which R and R' can be =S or =O, or a variety of other groups.
A tetracyclic triterpenoid that is lanosta-8,24-diene substituted by a beta-hydroxy group at the 3beta position. It is the compound from which all steroids are derived.
A trihydroxybenzoic acid that is benzoic acid substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2, 4 and 6.
A benzoate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-hydroxybenzoic acid with methanol.
